proof: the generic Tensor arm computes Literal::from_f64(float_op(f64::from_bits(b))) for F64Bits; eval_unary_f64_tensor_fast_path computes Literal::F64Bits(float_op(f64::from_bits(b)).to_bits()), and from_f64(x) == F64Bits(x.to_bits()), so bits are identical. Edge cases preserved: square(-0.0)=+0.0 (index 2 = 0), sign(-0.0)=-0.0 (sign index 2 = 0x8000000000000000), NaN->NaN (canonical), +-inf squared=+inf, sign(+-inf)=+-1.0. Non-F64 tensors fall through to the generic per-element variant match.
